      <h1>Tax-Loss Harvesting Explained: Save Thousands on Investment Taxes</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">I first learned about tax-loss harvesting when I got a $4,200 tax bill on investment gains I hadn't even cashed out yet. That stung. Turns out, if I'd sold some underperforming positions earlier that year, I could have offset those gains and saved a big chunk of that bill. It's not complicated once you understand the rules, but nobody explained it to me in plain English — so here's the guide I wish I'd had. I'll cover how it works, the wash-sale rule that trips people up, and the situations where it actually backfires.</p>
    </header>

